### Mission

.eco is an inclusive and welcoming home for the global environmental community. Our community consists of over 6,800 businesses, non-profits, individuals and others committed to making positive change for our planet.

### 2025 Impact Highlights

Here are a few of the key accomplishments this year:

* Released [climate reports](/news/climate-reporting-for-eco-domains/) for every .eco domain name
* Compiled and compared the [carbon footprint of domain registries](/news/carbon-footprint-of-domain-registries/)
* [Highlighted domain retailers](/news/eco-friendly-web-host/) powered by renewable energy, with a low <abbr title="Power usage effectiveness">PUE</abbr>, and recycling their e-waste
* Collaborated with the [Green Web Foundation](https://www.thegreenwebfoundation.org/) on [Green Web Tracker](https://tracker.greenweb.org/) and [carbon.txt](https://carbontxt.org/)
* [Celebrated the .eco community](/news/leaning-into-community/) by featuring 10 [.eco champions](/champions/)
* Refocused on helping to meet the [UN Sustainable Development Goals](/news/aligning-with-the-sdgs/)
* Raised the alarm about the security risk of [invalid nameservers](/news/security-risk-of-invalid-nameservers/)
* Published our [calendar of 26 environmental events](/news/eco-event-calendar/) we celebrated this year
* Exited Twitter and shared our approach to [engaging on social media](/news/social-media-strategy-2025/). 

### 2025 Goals

At the start of this year, we set three main impact goals for ourselves:

* Share greenhouse gas footprints for each .eco domain
* Certify to the ISO 14068 carbon neutral standard
* Make SBTi Net Zero commitment

Publishing [climate reports for every .eco domain](/news/climate-reporting-for-eco-domains/) was something that we started thinking about once we began measuring our own climate footprint and realized how difficult it can be to obtain reporting data from our partners and suppliers. We wanted to lead by example and be transparent to the .eco community about the impact of operating their .eco domain. So we were excited to release these new climate reports in time for .eco's birthday in April. While a [few other domain registries](/news/carbon-footprint-of-domain-registries/) have measured their own greenhouse gas emissions and estimated the average emissions per domain, .eco climate reports are the first time that the domain industry has produced a custom climate report per domain that is tailored to the DNS traffic that domain receives.

In prior years, we certified that our operations are carbon neutral based on the [PAS 2060 standard](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSI_PAS_2060). That standard has been superseded by [ISO 14068](https://www.iso.org/standard/43279.html), which is more stringent in terms of prioritizing emissions reduction and the types of eligible carbon credits. We are just wrapping up this certification and will have more news to share about it in early 2026.

Unfortunately, we did not make progress registering our climate targets with SBTi. We did focus on a broad range of other initiatives as covered in the [2025 Highlights](#2025-impact-highlights), but we didn't get to this one.

