### Community

The .eco community has continued to grow over the course of 2025 and now consists of over 6,800 members from all around the world. We are heartened to see this continued growth even as many nations backslide on their environmental commitments and ambitions.

Part of our role as stewards of the .eco community is highlighting the inspiring work done by our members. Through the [.eco Champions Programme](/champions/) we turn the spotlight on community members and help amplify their story through the case studies on our website and in our newsletters. In 2025, we featured **10 .eco champions** &mdash; the most in any year since we started the programme. If you would like to nominate a community member to be featured, <a class="chat-link" href="#">please get in touch</a>.

To keep the community updated about what’s new with .eco, we send out an email newsletter every three months. We also provide a [Slack community](/community/slack/) to serve as a forum for .eco community members to communicate directly, share what they’re working on and give feedback. Since launching on Slack in 2023, we’ve grown to over 300 members.

