### Impact Goals for 2026

Here are a few additional ways that we will be working to expand the impact of .eco in 2026:

#### Do more in support of the SDGs

There are fewer than 5 years left to meet the 17 UN Sustainable Development Goals. The SDGs are a core pillar of the .eco community: everyone with a .eco profile needs to identify the SDGs that they are working to support. We recognize that we have not done enough to support the .eco community in helping to meet the SDG goals. This year we will work to rectify that.

#### Encourage domain retailers to back Green Web Check

As mentioned above, we have started working with our partners to encourage them to certify with the Green Web Foundation if they are using a data center powered by renewable energy. As electricity grids use more low carbon energy, it should be increasingly attainable for hosting providers to show they're green.

#### Foster more collaboration between .eco members

The impact of our actions increase exponentially if we can do more to work together as a community. In 2026, we have plans to expand the opportunities for you to partner with other members of the .eco community. We are excited to share more with you in 2026!

#### Dark mode

One thing that we didn't talk much about is that we added support for dark mode on this website. We did this both to make the website more accessible to visitors with sensitivity to bright displays and to reduce the energy use of viewing the site. Work to support dark mode for the .eco profile system is in progress and we hope to roll this out in 2026.

